01:23:13.229 --> 01:23:15.714
- Yeah. bye. Mike.
- It's okay. Mother.

1751
01:23:18.476 --> 01:23:20.926
Just couldn't give him
one night. huh?

1752
01:23:21.065 --> 01:23:22.549
[Tito scoffs]

1753
01:23:22.687 --> 01:23:23.999
JOSEPH:
What?

1754
01:23:24.137 --> 01:23:25.517
[laughs softly]

1755
01:23:26.587 --> 01:23:29.349
JOSEPH: So. now
let me get this straight. Don.

1756
01:23:29.487 --> 01:23:30.798
Ten. 11 or 12?

1757
01:23:30.936 --> 01:23:32.938
How many wins do you have?
You. uh...

1758
01:23:33.077 --> 01:23:37.046
That's 13 of the current world
champions that I've promoted.

1759
01:23:37.184 --> 01:23:40.118
We got 110 fighters
in our stable right now.

1760
01:23:40.256 --> 01:23:42.051
But I'm gonna
tell you this. all right?

1761
01:23:42.189 --> 01:23:44.743
The big business
that's gonna be booming?

1762
01:23:45.537 --> 01:23:47.298
The lightweight class.

1763
01:23:47.436 --> 01:23:49.921
I'm gonna take those young
stars all the way to the top.

1764
01:23:50.059 --> 01:23:51.612
- Yeah. you are. [laughs]
- Yeah.

1765
01:23:51.750 --> 01:23:54.788
- Life is good. my friend.
- Yes. it is.

1766
01:23:54.926 --> 01:23:56.376
- [both laughing]
- Yes. it is.

1767
01:23:56.514 --> 01:23:58.447
Those Cubans.
straight from Castro himself.

1768
01:23:58.585 --> 01:23:59.689
- All right. [sniffs]
- Yes.

1769
01:23:59.827 --> 01:24:02.347
- Yes. yes. yes. yes.
- Oh. yes.

1770
01:24:02.485 --> 01:24:04.177
Now...

1771
01:24:04.315 --> 01:24:06.558
what did you want
to talk to me about?

1772
01:24:10.079 --> 01:24:12.944
Have you thought about getting
into the music business?

1773
01:24:13.082 --> 01:24:16.396
- Crossover-type thing?
- I don't follow you.

1774
01:24:17.259 --> 01:24:19.088
Well. I'm about to take

1775
01:24:19.226 --> 01:24:20.848
- my boys on a world tour.
- Hmm.

1776
01:24:20.986 --> 01:24:22.505
You know. we're gonna start
with North America.

1777
01:24:22.643 --> 01:24:24.128
- You know. stadiums only.
- Hmm.

1778
01:24:24.266 --> 01:24:26.095
You know. the biggest.

1779
01:24:26.233 --> 01:24:28.477
It's time to show the world
that the Jacksons are back.

1780
01:24:28.615 --> 01:24:30.651
- Right on. Okay.
- And bigger than ever.

1781
01:24:30.789 --> 01:24:32.101
You've seen them sales
on Thriller.

1782
01:24:32.239 --> 01:24:33.620
- Huh?
- Mm-hmm.

1783
01:24:33.758 --> 01:24:34.828
People are gonna be
climbing the walls.

1784
01:24:34.966 --> 01:24:37.106
[both laughing]

1785
01:24:38.107 --> 01:24:40.144
Is Michael gonna be there?

1786
01:24:42.284 --> 01:24:44.009
[lighter snaps shut]

1787
01:24:44.148 --> 01:24:45.804
Of course Michael's
gonna be there.

1788
01:24:45.942 --> 01:24:47.772
Hmm. That's good to hear.

1789
01:24:48.635 --> 01:24:50.740
Now. what's in it for me?

1790
01:24:53.295 --> 01:24:54.848
I've been watching you. Don.

1791
01:24:54.986 --> 01:24:56.815
- I watch you like a hawk.
- Hmm. [chuckles]

1792
01:24:56.953 --> 01:24:59.335
I love the way
you promote your fighters.

1793
01:24:59.473 --> 01:25:01.337
- Uh-huh.
- You're the king of marketing.

1794
01:25:01.475 --> 01:25:04.064
You know. I just. uh.
I think that you and I.

1795
01:25:04.202 --> 01:25:06.308
if we came together.
we could. uh...

1796
01:25:07.550 --> 01:25:09.069
...we could form
a good partnership.

1797
01:25:09.207 --> 01:25:10.588
Me and you?

1798
01:25:10.726 --> 01:25:12.555
I'll cut you a good deal.

1799
01:25:12.693 --> 01:25:15.489
- I like deals.
- [sets down lighter]

1800
01:25:21.461 --> 01:25:23.152
I need...

1801
01:25:23.290 --> 01:25:24.878
this for my boys.

1802
01:25:25.534 --> 01:25:27.018
I need it.

1803
01:25:27.156 --> 01:25:29.469
You know. I-I think
they deserve the-the...

1804
01:25:29.607 --> 01:25:31.091
Rolls-Royce of sponsorships.

1805
01:25:31.229 --> 01:25:34.232
I mean. merchandising.
marketing. you hear me?

1806
01:25:34.370 --> 01:25:35.647
I mean. it's got to be huge.

1807
01:25:35.785 --> 01:25:38.650
And only you and I could do it.

1808
01:25:39.513 --> 01:25:41.412
It'll be called...

1809
01:25:41.550 --> 01:25:44.518
- the Victory tour.
- Hmm.

1810
01:25:44.656 --> 01:25:46.486
[sucks teeth]

1811
01:25:46.624 --> 01:25:48.315
[clicks tongue]

1812
01:25:48.453 --> 01:25:50.214
I may have something for you.

1813
01:25:50.352 --> 01:25:51.732
Pepsi.

1814
01:25:51.870 --> 01:25:53.907
They want to get
back in the game.

1815
01:25:54.045 --> 01:25:55.874
Michael could be
the face of the brand.

1816
01:25:56.012 --> 01:25:57.876
do some commercials.

1817
01:25:58.014 --> 01:26:00.016
- All right.
- [chuckles]

1818
01:26:00.155 --> 01:26:01.949
- I can see it.
- Yeah.

1819
01:26:03.468 --> 01:26:05.056
But you wouldn't be
bullshitting me.

1820
01:26:05.194 --> 01:26:06.506
would you. Joe?

1821
01:26:07.645 --> 01:26:10.820
'Cause if you
can't get Michael...

1822
01:26:14.583 --> 01:26:16.861
[dramatic music playing on TV]

1823
01:26:20.382 --> 01:26:22.038
[Katherine laughing]

1824
01:26:22.177 --> 01:26:24.662
Now. that... now. that's
my favorite part. [laughs]

1825
01:26:30.737 --> 01:26:32.566
I'm gonna
leave it to you. Michael.

1826
01:26:32.704 --> 01:26:33.912
You can't go yet.

1827
01:26:34.050 --> 01:26:35.776
No.
I'm going to bed. I'm tired.

1828
01:26:35.914 --> 01:26:37.261
You got to stay for the ending.
That's the best part.

1829
01:26:37.399 --> 01:26:39.573
Your mother is tired. baby.

1830
01:26:40.367 --> 01:26:43.025
Do me a favor. Make sure
you turn the lights off?

1831
01:26:43.163 --> 01:26:44.958
- Night. Mother.
- Good night.

1832
01:26:45.096 --> 01:26:47.202
[music continues on TV]

1833
01:26:49.480 --> 01:26:50.722
[chuckles]

1834
01:26:50.860 --> 01:26:53.173
[humming softly]

1835
01:26:54.795 --> 01:26:56.521
[switch clicks]

1836
01:26:57.695 --> 01:26:59.421
[humming continues]

1837
01:26:59.559 --> 01:27:01.871
[vocalizing softly]

1838
01:27:13.745 --> 01:27:15.609
[vocalizing continues]

1839
01:27:15.747 --> 01:27:17.162
[gasps]

1840
01:27:20.545 --> 01:27:22.616
Why are you here?

1841
01:27:23.755 --> 01:27:26.068
What? Can't a father
visit his son?

1842
01:27:28.277 --> 01:27:30.866
Biggest-selling record
of all time.

1843
01:27:31.004 --> 01:27:33.489
from a poor kid from Gary.

1844
01:27:33.627 --> 01:27:35.422
Who would have thought?

1845
01:27:36.251 --> 01:27:38.632
Me. I thought.

1846
01:27:38.770 --> 01:27:40.807
[chuckles]

1847
01:27:43.982 --> 01:27:45.674
Come here.

1848
01:27:46.778 --> 01:27:48.918
Joseph. I know
you want something.

1849
01:27:53.647 --> 01:27:55.270
Michael...

1850
01:27:56.685 --> 01:27:59.308
...I'm gonna need you
to tour with your brothers.

1851
01:28:00.551 --> 01:28:03.070
Now. I let you do
that album by yourself.

1852
01:28:04.175 --> 01:28:06.281
I'm gonna need you
to do this for me.

1853
01:28:07.937 --> 01:28:09.491
For your family.

1854
01:28:10.561 --> 01:28:12.666
I'm not a child anymore. Joseph.

1855
01:28:12.804 --> 01:28:14.289
[sighs heavily]

1856
01:28:14.427 --> 01:28:15.669
- And you're not my manager.
- Here we go.

1857
01:28:15.807 --> 01:28:17.982
I have to start
living my own life.

1858
01:28:19.363 --> 01:28:21.157
On my own.

1859
01:28:21.986 --> 01:28:23.746
Just like everyone else.

1860
01:28:23.884 --> 01:28:25.783
You ain't like everyone else.

1861
01:28:27.474 --> 01:28:29.200
So. you're trying to tell me

1862
01:28:29.338 --> 01:28:31.651
you want to be treated
like an adult?

1863
01:28:32.548 --> 01:28:33.998
All right.

1864
01:28:34.136 --> 01:28:37.829
You want to
see what the world is like...

1865
01:28:38.623 --> 01:28:41.246
...without a family
that protects you.

1866
01:28:41.385 --> 01:28:42.834
[hinges creaking]

1867
01:28:42.972 --> 01:28:45.043
Without a family that...

1868
01:28:45.181 --> 01:28:46.735
understands you.

1869
01:28:47.701 --> 01:28:50.877
Nobody else will understand you
outside this place.

1870
01:28:51.015 --> 01:28:53.983
There you'll be with
all the money in the world.

1871
01:28:54.121 --> 01:28:56.676
surrounded by people
who'll say "yes"

1872
01:28:56.814 --> 01:28:59.195
to everything.

1873
01:29:00.852 --> 01:29:03.199
Is that what you want?

1874
01:29:06.444 --> 01:29:08.343
What kind of sense that make?

1875
01:29:15.626 --> 01:29:17.904
I'm gonna...

1876
01:29:18.042 --> 01:29:19.664
call Don King

1877
01:29:19.802 --> 01:29:22.357
and tell him
you're doing the tour.

1878
01:29:24.359 --> 01:29:27.016
I know you don't want
to let your family down.

1879
01:29:29.674 --> 01:29:31.883
[Michael breathing deeply]

1880
01:29:35.197 --> 01:29:37.061
[door closes]

1881
01:29:38.165 --> 01:29:40.375
♪ ♪

1882
01:29:45.897 --> 01:29:47.554
[sighs]

1883
01:29:49.556 --> 01:29:50.833
[crowd cheering loudly]

1884
01:29:50.971 --> 01:29:53.698
["Billie Jean" playing]

1885
01:29:58.013 --> 01:30:00.256
♪ You're a whole
new generation ♪

1886
01:30:00.395 --> 01:30:02.362
♪ You're lovin' what you do ♪

1887
01:30:02.500 --> 01:30:04.433
♪ Put a Pepsi in the motion ♪

1888
01:30:04.571 --> 01:30:06.401
♪ That choice is up to you.
hey-ey ♪

1889
01:30:06.539 --> 01:30:08.403
- DIRECTOR: Cut! Cut! Cut! Cut!
- ♪ You're the Pepsi... ♪

1890
01:30:08.541 --> 01:30:10.266
- [music stops]
- MAN: We're cutting. guys.

1891
01:30:11.129 --> 01:30:14.098
All right. here's what I need.
I'm thinking...

1892
01:30:15.651 --> 01:30:17.619
...I'm gonna move the camera in
while you're up here.

1893
01:30:18.136 --> 01:30:21.277
I need to get a close-up
of you at the top.

1894
01:30:21.416 --> 01:30:23.107
so just feel the camera
as you come down.

1895
01:30:23.245 --> 01:30:25.109
- Okay.
- Okay. great. All right.

1896
01:30:25.247 --> 01:30:26.317
DIRECTOR:
Okay. everybody.

1897
01:30:26.455 --> 01:30:27.767
[grunts] Here we go.

1898
01:30:27.905 --> 01:30:30.666
What is this?
What do we got. take six?

1899
01:30:30.804 --> 01:30:32.841
- [groans quietly]
- Lucky six. Lucky six.

1900
01:30:32.979 --> 01:30:34.532
Here we go. Energy. everybody!

1901
01:30:34.670 --> 01:30:37.155
You love the Jacksons.
You love the Jacksons.

1902
01:30:37.293 --> 01:30:39.192
You love Pepsi. Let's go!

1903
01:30:39.330 --> 01:30:41.677
- WOMAN: A marker!
- [marker snaps]

1904
01:30:41.815 --> 01:30:43.127
- MAN 2: B mark!
- [marker snaps]

1905
01:30:43.265 --> 01:30:44.853
- MAN 3: C mark.
- [audience cheering]

1906
01:30:44.991 --> 01:30:46.820
- [marker snaps]
- DIRECTOR: And playback.

1907
01:30:46.958 --> 01:30:50.341
["Billie Jean" playing]

1908
01:30:53.137 --> 01:30:55.173
[fireworks explode]

1909
01:31:04.597 --> 01:31:06.081
- [music fades]
- [sizzling]

1910
01:31:06.219 --> 01:31:07.427
[muffled cheering]

1911
01:31:07.565 --> 01:31:09.774
[distorted whimpering]

1912
01:31:09.912 --> 01:31:12.294
[distorted moaning]

1913
01:31:13.502 --> 01:31:14.917
- [music resumes]
- [screaming]

1914
01:31:15.055 --> 01:31:16.332
Cut it.

1915
01:31:16.471 --> 01:31:18.127
- MAN: Put it out!
- [Michael groaning]

1916
01:31:18.265 --> 01:31:19.370
[microphone feedback]

1917
01:31:19.508 --> 01:31:21.372
- [groaning]
- TITO: Michael!

1918
01:31:21.510 --> 01:31:22.960
- [clamoring. screaming]
- [groaning]

1919
01:31:23.098 --> 01:31:25.169
- What happened?
- [moaning]

1920
01:31:25.307 --> 01:31:27.033
- BILL: Back up. back up. back up.
- Bill. get him out of here.

1921
01:31:27.171 --> 01:31:29.518
BILL: I'm here. I'm here.
I'm here. Michael.

1922
01:31:29.656 --> 01:31:31.382
- Get him up. get him up.
- I'm here. Joker. I'm here.

1923
01:31:31.520 --> 01:31:33.280
Hey. you're gonna be okay.
okay? You're gonna be okay.

1924
01:31:33.418 --> 01:31:34.765
BILL:
Come on. Mike. Clear a path!

1925
01:31:34.903 --> 01:31:36.974
[people screaming and clamoring]

1926
01:31:38.009 --> 01:31:40.874
Out of my way!
Michael. I'm coming!

1927
01:31:41.392 --> 01:31:43.014
- [moans]
- Get back! Get out of my way!

1928
01:31:43.152 --> 01:31:45.500
Clear a path!
Get back! Get back!

1929
01:31:46.742 --> 01:31:49.849
Clear a path!
Move! Move. please!

1930
01:31:49.987 --> 01:31:52.541
[muffled shouting and wailing]

1931
01:31:52.679 --> 01:31:54.647
BILL:
Excuse me!

1932
01:31:55.544 --> 01:31:57.201
[whimpering]

1933
01:31:57.339 --> 01:31:59.514
♪ ♪

1934
01:32:06.969 --> 01:32:08.902
[phone ringing]

1935
01:32:09.040 --> 01:32:10.525
[Joseph exhales]

1936
01:32:11.629 --> 01:32:13.873
[continues tapping fingers]

1937
01:32:17.393 --> 01:32:19.706
[indistinct P.A. announcement]

1938
01:32:24.366 --> 01:32:26.506
Hey. Kate. come on.

1939
01:32:28.439 --> 01:32:29.820
Hey. I need to talk to you.

1940
01:32:29.958 --> 01:32:31.615
- Sir.
- I'm his father. Joseph Jackson.

1941
01:32:31.753 --> 01:32:33.513
This is his mother. Katherine.

1942
01:32:33.651 --> 01:32:35.584
- Hi. It's good to meet you.
- Very nice to meet you.

1943
01:32:35.722 --> 01:32:36.965
Thank you.

1944
01:32:37.103 --> 01:32:38.622
Well. your son is
in stable condition.

1945
01:32:38.760 --> 01:32:40.451
- All right.
- DOCTOR: All right?

1946
01:32:40.589 --> 01:32:43.143
And. uh. we're trying to bring
his heart rate down.

1947
01:32:43.281 --> 01:32:45.111
but he's in a lot of pain.

1948
01:32:46.250 --> 01:32:47.596
Okay. When will he recover?

1949
01:32:47.734 --> 01:32:49.149
It's too soon to tell.

1950
01:32:49.287 --> 01:32:51.324
It's gonna be
a long road. all right?

1951
01:32:51.462 --> 01:32:55.121
He has third-degree burns
and substantial nerve damage.

1952
01:32:56.122 --> 01:32:57.951
JOSEPH:
Okay.

1953
01:32:58.849 --> 01:33:01.748
Do you think he'll ever be
able to perform again?

1954
01:33:01.886 --> 01:33:03.232
Ever?

1955
01:33:03.370 --> 01:33:05.096
KATHERINE:
Joseph.

1956
01:33:07.720 --> 01:33:11.378
Mr. Jackson.
your son almost died.

1957
01:33:11.516 --> 01:33:12.932
I know that.

1958
01:33:13.070 --> 01:33:14.865
Well. if that fire
had caught his clothes.

1959
01:33:15.003 --> 01:33:17.764
or burned over to his face
and eyes. he wouldn't be here.

1960
01:33:17.902 --> 01:33:19.490
I know my boy.

1961
01:33:19.628 --> 01:33:21.768
And the only thing
that's gonna heal him

1962
01:33:21.906 --> 01:33:23.494
is by getting
back on that stage.

1963
01:33:24.806 --> 01:33:26.428
That's where he lives.

1964
01:33:26.566 --> 01:33:28.154
- DOCTOR: I understand that. sir.
- LA TOYA: Oh. my God.

1965
01:33:28.292 --> 01:33:29.604
- But it's gonna be a while.
- Do you? All right.

1966
01:33:29.742 --> 01:33:31.640
DOCTOR:
Yes. I do. But. Mr. Jackson...

1967
01:33:31.778 --> 01:33:34.988
he's gonna need
your support to get there.

1968
01:33:35.126 --> 01:33:36.818
I'm sorry.

1969
01:33:39.130 --> 01:33:40.891
[exhales]

1970
01:33:41.719 --> 01:33:43.203
WOMAN [shouting in distance]:
Praying for you. Michael!

1971
01:33:43.341 --> 01:33:45.136
DOCTOR: It's unlikely
that will grow back.

1972
01:33:45.689 --> 01:33:48.899
You'll need surgery
to laser the scar tissue

1973
01:33:49.037 --> 01:33:51.902
and stretch part of the scalp
over the burn.

1974
01:33:52.730 --> 01:33:55.733
All right? We'll insert an
implant to protect the scalp.

1975
01:33:55.871 --> 01:33:57.873
Will I have to wear a wig?

1976
01:33:58.011 --> 01:33:59.944
Well. right there on top.

1977
01:34:02.015 --> 01:34:04.466
What kind of wig?
Like. a full wig?

1978
01:34:04.604 --> 01:34:06.054
Hard to say.

1979
01:34:06.192 --> 01:34:08.125
There are prosthetic
hair weaves we can try.

1980
01:34:08.263 --> 01:34:11.507
but we won't know till we see
how the surgery goes next week.

1981
01:34:14.027 --> 01:34:16.305
[indistinct P.A. announcement]

1982
01:34:17.962 --> 01:34:19.481
[crowd shouting indistinctly
in the distance]

1983
01:34:19.619 --> 01:34:21.241
You'll. um...

1984
01:34:21.379 --> 01:34:23.830
you'll have to stay
on the Demerol for a while.

1985
01:34:23.968 --> 01:34:25.798
I don't want to take medication.

1986
01:34:25.936 --> 01:34:27.834
I have to be honest.
Mr. Jackson.

1987
01:34:27.972 --> 01:34:29.456
you're gonna need them.

1988
01:34:30.043 --> 01:34:32.356
We have to replace
the implant periodically.

1989
01:34:32.494 --> 01:34:34.427
The nerves are exposed up there.

1990
01:34:34.565 --> 01:34:36.567
You'll be in a lot of pain.

1991
01:34:39.087 --> 01:34:42.055
I'll let you rest.
but I'll be back later.

1992
01:34:47.543 --> 01:34:50.098
WOMAN: We'll stay here
till you're better. Michael!

1993
01:34:50.236 --> 01:34:51.720
REPORTER:
You see the number of people

1994
01:34:51.858 --> 01:34:53.929
who have already gathered
outside the hospital.

1995
01:34:54.067 --> 01:34:55.310
If that isn't a testament

1996
01:34:55.448 --> 01:34:57.036
to the star power
